e skills in the forge to aid the resistance if they have any chance of defending against the looming Pandesian invasion. He is awestruck when he encounters Dierdre, the strongest girl he has ever met. This time she has a chance to make a stand against Pandesia, and as she bravely faces off, she wonders if her father and his men will have her back this time.Vesuvius leads his Troll nation across a vulnerable Escalon, devastating the land, while Theos, enraged at what becomes of his son, is on a rampage himself, and will not stop until all of Escalon is aflame.With its strong atmosphere and complex characters, THE WEIGHT OF HONOR is a sweeping saga of knights and warriors, of kings and lords, of honor and valor, of magic, destiny, monsters and dragons. It is a story of love and broken hearts, of deception, ambition and betrayal. It is fantasy at its finest, inviting us into a world that will live with us forever, one that will appeal to all ages and genders.Book #4 in KINGS AND SORCERERS will be published soon.â€œIf you thought that there was no reason left for living after the end of the Sorcererâ€™s Ring series, you were wrong. Morgan Rice has come up with what promises to be another brilliant series, immersing us in a fantasy of trolls and dragons, of valor, honor, courage, magic and faith in your destiny. Morgan has managed again to produce a strong set of characters that make us cheer for them on every page.â€¦Recommended for the permanent library of all readers that love a well-written fantasy.â€--Books and Movie Reviews, Roberto Mattos (regarding Rise of the Dragons)â€œ[The novel] succeedsâ€”right from the startâ€¦. A superior fantasyâ€¦It begins, as it should, with one protagonist\'s struggles and moves neatly into a wider circle of knights, dragons, magic and monsters, and destiny.â€¦All the trappings of high fantasy are here, from soldiers and battles to confrontations with selfâ€¦.A recommended winner for any who enjoy epic fantasy writing fueled by powerf